and drags it into the space.

311
00:25:02,611 --> 00:25:06,791
The dragging of the magnetic field
by the plasma is a result

312
00:25:06,791 --> 00:25:10,871
of the frozen flux theorem
that you have seen in module 3G.

313
00:25:11,349 --> 00:25:16,055
The dragged magnetic field forms
the interplanetary magnetic field [IMF]

314
00:25:16,459 --> 00:25:19,567
The interplanetary magnetic field
is quite weak.

315
00:25:19,916 --> 00:25:22,498
At the earth's orbit it's about

316
00:25:22,498 --> 00:25:26,825
1 over 10,000 times the field
at the Earth's surface.

317
00:25:27,149 --> 00:25:33,090
However, it exerts an extraordinary
influence on the Earth's magnetosphere.

318
00:25:39,931 --> 00:25:44,208
The magnetic field of the Earth
provides an effective obstacle

319
00:25:44,208 --> 00:25:45,953
to the solar wind plasma.

320
00:25:46,469 --> 00:25:49,037
When it reaches the Earth's orbit,

321
00:25:49,796 --> 00:25:52,882
the solar wind is quite rarified

322
00:25:53,134 --> 00:25:57,275
between 3 and 8
ions per cubic centimeter.

323
00:26:02,299 --> 00:26:06,247
The Earth's magnetic field
keeps the ions,

324
00:26:06,247 --> 00:26:09,781
keeps the plasma out of the Earth

325
00:26:09,781 --> 00:26:13,016
by carving its own cavity
in the solar wind.

326
00:26:13,016 --> 00:26:17,910
This region is called the magnetosphere
although it is not spherical.

327
00:26:18,532 --> 00:26:21,469
When it reaches the Earth's
magnetic field, the solar wind,

328
00:26:21,469 --> 00:26:24,920
as we have seen,
is usually supersonic

329
00:26:24,920 --> 00:26:27,082
and the magnetic field of the Earth

330
00:26:28,085 --> 00:26:32,677
creates a magnetic obstacle
which creates a shock front

331
00:26:32,677 --> 00:26:35,436
where the plasma becomes subsonic.

332
00:26:36,019 --> 00:26:39,176
This region is called <i>bow shock region</i>.

333
00:26:40,496 --> 00:26:45,497
The bow shock region is approximately 
17 kilometers thick,

334
00:26:45,497 --> 00:26:48,282
and it is located at a distance

335
00:26:48,282 --> 00:26:52,849
of approximately
90,000 kilometers from earth.

336
00:26:56,070 --> 00:27:01,316
Most of the solar wind plasma is heated
and slows down at the bow shock

337
00:27:01,961 --> 00:27:03,918
and detours around the earth.

338
00:27:04,949 --> 00:27:10,494
Some plasma of the solar wind penetrates
inside the magnetic field of the earth

339
00:27:10,494 --> 00:27:13,019
and forms the so called <i>magnetosheath</i>.

340
00:27:16,778 --> 00:27:22,453
The magnetosheath exerts a pressure
on the Earth's magnetic field.

341
00:27:23,443 --> 00:27:27,731
The region where the pressure
of the magnetic field

342
00:27:27,731 --> 00:27:30,790
equals the pressure
of the magnetosheath,

343
00:27:30,790 --> 00:27:33,764
this is called <i>the magnetopause</i>.

344
00:27:34,790 --> 00:27:39,658
By dragging the magnetic field lines
of the Earth's magnetic field with it,

345
00:27:40,186 --> 00:27:43,959
the solar wind deforms
the magnetic field lines

346
00:27:43,959 --> 00:27:47,203
and creates a neutral sheath

347
00:27:47,203 --> 00:27:50,672
where the magnetic field lines
are opposite directed.

348
00:27:53,816 --> 00:27:55,664
As we have seen in previous modules

349
00:27:56,238 --> 00:28:01,790
where opposite directed magnetic field
lines come together,

350
00:28:01,790 --> 00:28:06,795
magnetic reconnection can take place
if the magnetic field lines

351
00:28:06,795 --> 00:28:09,482
are pushed together strongly enough.

352
00:28:13,986 --> 00:28:17,986
One of the most important
perturbations to the solar wind

353
00:28:17,986 --> 00:28:22,548
are coronal mass ejections
or in short, CME's.

354
00:28:23,327 --> 00:28:29,139
During a coronal mass ejection,
the Sun can eject 10¹²

355
00:28:29,139 --> 00:28:34,817
up to 10¹³ kg
of plasma moving at speeds

356
00:28:34,817 --> 00:28:38,811
of approximately 1,000 km/s.

357
00:28:39,362 --> 00:28:43,727
These are strong perturbations
to the solar wind which can have

358
00:28:43,727 --> 00:28:46,526
profound consequences on earth.

359
00:28:48,235 --> 00:28:51,725
By pushing together
the magnetic field lines

360
00:28:51,725 --> 00:28:55,964
at the neutral sheath, 
reconnection can occur

361
00:28:55,964 --> 00:28:59,376
and plasmas and electrons
can be accelerated

362
00:28:59,376 --> 00:29:01,754
and reach down earth,

363
00:29:01,754 --> 00:29:06,215
creating one of the most
spectacular events on earth,

364
00:29:06,215 --> 00:29:08,601
which is the <i>aurora borealis</i>.

